The paper deals with the problem of computing a sparse approximation to the Fourier transform of a signal, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm presented in the paper has a sublinear runtime, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The problem of sparse Fourier transform is also related to compressed sensing, which falls under the category of cs.DS. Finally, the paper presents a new technique for achieving nearly optimal sample complexity, which may be of interest to researchers working in the field of statistical inference (cs.SI).
